If the plants are the usual types that you know how to care for, this won't be such an issue as being expected to care for plants in need of special fertilizing or watering regimes. Things to ask include:
Do any of the plants require more or less water than every day? {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/d/d3/Take-Care-of-Your-Neighbor%27s-Plants-While-They%27re-Away-Step-1Bullet1.jpg/v4-460px-Take-Care-of-Your-Neighbor%27s-Plants-While-They%27re-Away-Step-1Bullet1.jpg","bigUrl":"/images/thumb/d/d3/Take-Care-of-Your-Neighbor%27s-Plants-While-They%27re-Away-Step-1Bullet1.jpg/aid1549426-v4-728px-Take-Care-of-Your-Neighbor%27s-Plants-While-They%27re-Away-Step-1Bullet1.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":"728","bigHeight":"546","licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Do any of the plants require shifting for the purposes of sunlight/shade/temperature? Or perhaps there is a need to move a shade cloth, or open a window, etc. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/6/62/Take-Care-of-Your-Neighbor%27s-Plants-While-They%27re-Away-Step-1Bullet2.jpg/v4-460px-Take-Care-of-Your-Neighbor%27s-Plants-While-They%27re-Away-Step-1Bullet2.jpg","bigUrl":"/images/thumb/6/62/Take-Care-of-Your-Neighbor%27s-Plants-While-They%27re-Away-Step-1Bullet2.jpg/aid1549426-v4-728px-Take-Care-of-Your-Neighbor%27s-Plants-While-They%27re-Away-Step-1Bullet2.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":"728","bigHeight":"546","licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Will any of the plants need deadheading (removal of blooms), removal of anything in the time you're in charge? {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/b/b5/Take-Care-of-Your-Neighbor%27s-Plants-While-They%27re-Away-Step-1Bullet3.jpg/v4-460px-Take-Care-of-Your-Neighbor%27s-Plants-While-They%27re-Away-Step-1Bullet3.jpg","bigUrl":"/images/thumb/b/b5/Take-Care-of-Your-Neighbor%27s-Plants-While-They%27re-Away-Step-1Bullet3.jpg/aid1549426-v4-728px-Take-Care-of-Your-Neighbor%27s-Plants-While-They%27re-Away-Step-1Bullet3.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":"728","bigHeight":"546","licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Do any plants need misting as well as/instead of watering? Some tropical or delicate species prefer misting over direct watering. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/9/9d/Take-Care-of-Your-Neighbor%27s-Plants-While-They%27re-Away-Step-1Bullet4.jpg/v4-460px-Take-Care-of-Your-Neighbor%27s-Plants-While-They%27re-Away-Step-1Bullet4.jpg","bigUrl":"/images/thumb/9/9d/Take-Care-of-Your-Neighbor%27s-Plants-While-They%27re-Away-Step-1Bullet4.jpg/aid1549426-v4-728px-Take-Care-of-Your-Neighbor%27s-Plants-While-They%27re-Away-Step-1Bullet4.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":"728","bigHeight":"546","licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Are there particular things to watch out for and deal with, such as insect infestations or disease? If yes, what should you do to contain the problem? {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/d/d4/Take-Care-of-Your-Neighbor%27s-Plants-While-They%27re-Away-Step-1Bullet5.jpg/v4-460px-Take-Care-of-Your-Neighbor%27s-Plants-While-They%27re-Away-Step-1Bullet5.jpg","bigUrl":"/images/thumb/d/d4/Take-Care-of-Your-Neighbor%27s-Plants-While-They%27re-Away-Step-1Bullet5.jpg/aid1549426-v4-728px-Take-Care-of-Your-Neighbor%27s-Plants-While-They%27re-Away-Step-1Bullet5.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":"728","bigHeight":"546","licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Are you responsible for indoor and outdoor plants or just one or the other? {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/5/53/Take-Care-of-Your-Neighbor%27s-Plants-While-They%27re-Away-Step-1Bullet6.jpg/v4-460px-Take-Care-of-Your-Neighbor%27s-Plants-While-They%27re-Away-Step-1Bullet6.jpg","bigUrl":"/images/thumb/5/53/Take-Care-of-Your-Neighbor%27s-Plants-While-They%27re-Away-Step-1Bullet6.jpg/aid1549426-v4-728px-Take-Care-of-Your-Neighbor%27s-Plants-While-They%27re-Away-Step-1Bullet6.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":"728","bigHeight":"546","licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Do you need to know anything technical, such as timer switches for irrigation systems, etc.? If so, also ask what you do should the system fail––know who to call to get it fixed. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/5/54/Take-Care-of-Your-Neighbor%27s-Plants-While-They%27re-Away-Step-1Bullet7.jpg/v4-460px-Take-Care-of-Your-Neighbor%27s-Plants-While-They%27re-Away-Step-1Bullet7.jpg","bigUrl":"/images/thumb/5/54/Take-Care-of-Your-Neighbor%27s-Plants-While-They%27re-Away-Step-1Bullet7.jpg/aid1549426-v4-728px-Take-Care-of-Your-Neighbor%27s-Plants-While-They%27re-Away-Step-1Bullet7.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":"728","bigHeight":"546","licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Are there any other special requirements that you should be aware of? {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/8/80/Take-Care-of-Your-Neighbor%27s-Plants-While-They%27re-Away-Step-1Bullet8.jpg/v4-460px-Take-Care-of-Your-Neighbor%27s-Plants-While-They%27re-Away-Step-1Bullet8.jpg","bigUrl":"/images/thumb/8/80/Take-Care-of-Your-Neighbor%27s-Plants-While-They%27re-Away-Step-1Bullet8.jpg/aid1549426-v4-728px-Take-Care-of-Your-Neighbor%27s-Plants-While-They%27re-Away-Step-1Bullet8.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":"728","bigHeight":"546","licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

If pest infestations suddenly descend upon your neighbor's plants while they're away, do your best to defend the plants. Use chairs, tables, or anything else to block the plants from preventing deer or any other animal eating the plants. If they get in one day, try to find something else to block the animals from breaking in. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/b/ba/Take-Care-of-Your-Neighbor%27s-Plants-While-They%27re-Away-Step-9Bullet1.jpg/v4-460px-Take-Care-of-Your-Neighbor%27s-Plants-While-They%27re-Away-Step-9Bullet1.jpg","bigUrl":"/images/thumb/b/ba/Take-Care-of-Your-Neighbor%27s-Plants-While-They%27re-Away-Step-9Bullet1.jpg/aid1549426-v4-728px-Take-Care-of-Your-Neighbor%27s-Plants-While-They%27re-Away-Step-9Bullet1.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":"728","bigHeight":"546","licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Use organic pesticides, such as soap spray, to kill bugs such as aphids if there is an outbreak. Never use anything that might harm the plant; research online or ask at a garden center what you should do first. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/8/8b/Take-Care-of-Your-Neighbor%27s-Plants-While-They%27re-Away-Step-9Bullet2.jpg/v4-460px-Take-Care-of-Your-Neighbor%27s-Plants-While-They%27re-Away-Step-9Bullet2.jpg","bigUrl":"/images/thumb/8/8b/Take-Care-of-Your-Neighbor%27s-Plants-While-They%27re-Away-Step-9Bullet2.jpg/aid1549426-v4-728px-Take-Care-of-Your-Neighbor%27s-Plants-While-They%27re-Away-Step-9Bullet2.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":"728","bigHeight":"546","licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}
